This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for sentiment identification, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the development of a benchmark corpus, which can be considered as a resource for information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.CY).
